In [23]:
cross_table = pd.crosstab(final_df['designation'], final_df['work_type'], normalize='columns')

cross_table = cross_table.sort_values(by='On-site', ascending=False)

sns.set(style='darkgrid')
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))

cross_table.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=ax)

ax.set_title('Distribution of Designation and Work Type')
ax.set_xlabel('Designation')
ax.set_ylabel('Count')

ax.legend(title='Work Type')

plt.tight_layout()

plt.show()

Top 10 designations for each work type¶

In [24]:
wt = final_df.work_type.unique()
co=1
plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))
plt.suptitle('Top 10 Designations for each work type',fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
for i in wt:
    plt.subplot(2,3,co)
    pl = final_df[final_df['work_type'] == i]['designation'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    pl_filter = final_df[final_df['work_type'] == i]
    sns.countplot(data=pl_filter, x='designation', order=pl)
    plt.xlabel(i)
    plt.xticks(rotation=60)
    
    co+=1


plt.show()

In [25]:
wt = final_df.level.unique()
co = 1

plt.figure(figsize=(20,20 ))
plt.suptitle('Top 10 Designations for each Levels', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

for i in wt:
    plt.subplot(3, 3, co)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.7)
    
    pl = final_df[final_df['level'] == i]['designation'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    pl_filter = final_df[final_df['level'] == i]
    
    sns.countplot(data=pl_filter, x='designation',  order=pl)
    plt.xlabel(i)
    plt.xticks(rotation=60)
    
    co += 1


plt.show()

In [26]:
wt = final_df.level.unique()
co = 1

plt.figure(figsize=(20,20 ))
plt.suptitle('Top 10 Companies for each Levels', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

for i in wt:
    plt.subplot(3, 3, co)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.7)
    
    pl = final_df[final_df['level'] == i]['name'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    pl_filter = final_df[final_df['level'] == i]
    
    sns.countplot(data=pl_filter, x='name',  order=pl)
    plt.xlabel(i)
    plt.xticks(rotation=60)
    
    co += 1


plt.show()
In conclusion TCS provides highest associate level entry and EPAM Anywhere provides highest in mid senior level¶

In [27]:
wt = final_df.work_type.unique()
co=1
plt.figure(figsize=(20,8))
plt.suptitle('Top 10 Comapanies for each work type',fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
for i in wt:
    plt.subplot(2,3,co)
    pl = final_df[final_df['work_type'] == i]['name'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    pl_filter = final_df[final_df['work_type'] == i]
    sns.countplot(data=pl_filter, x='name', order=pl)
    plt.xlabel(i)
    plt.xticks(rotation=60)
    
    co+=1


plt.show()
In conclusion EPAM Anywhere provides highest Remote level jobs and TCS provides highest On-Site and Hybrid Level jobs¶
